{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~kobsa/courses/ICS104/course-notes/gdl-advance-info.htm", "content": "<!doctype html public \"-//w3c//dtd html 4.0 transitional//en\">\r<html>\r<head>\r   <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\">\r   <meta name=\"GENERATOR\" content=\"Mozilla/4.71 (Macintosh; I; PPC) [Netscape]\">\r   <title>gdl-advance-info.htm</title>\r</head>\r<body BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\">\r<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\"><b><font size=\"7\">Advance information</font></b></font></font> \r<ul> <li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>informs users about what \ris possible and what is not</font></font></li><li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>informs \rusers about what will happen</font></font></li><li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>give \rusers cues as to what action/input is correct</font></font></li><li> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>indicates \rforseeable inconveniences for the user</font></font></li></ul>\r<dl>\r  <dt><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2><i>Aim:</i>&nbsp; \r&nbsp;&nbsp;prevent users from performing actions that would lead to errors or otherwise </font></font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>unexpected \r    results.</font></font> <br> \r    <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2><i>Form:</i> \r    &nbsp;Advance information should be given through <i>visual indicators</i> rather than \r    text.</font></font> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"Text%20not%20read.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows a Yahoo calendar. The top entry reads &quot;Everybody please read this!&quot; Chances are that hardly any user will notice this alert since it is not visually supported.\"></a></font></font></font><br> \r&nbsp; </dt>\r</dl>\r<p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2><b>Examples</b>:</font></font> \r<ul> <li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>Menu entries which currently \rcannot be selected should be visually distinguished from entries that can be activated.</font></font></li><li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>Objects \rin direct-interactive interfaces that currently cannot be accessed should be visually \rdistinguished from objects that can be activated.</font></font></li><li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>The \rshape of the mouse symbol should indicate the action that will occur if the user \rclicks the mouse button. </font><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"advance-info-cursor.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows an assortment of different cursor shapes in the Macintosh operating system and the X-Windows widget set. This different shapes give advance information as to what will happen when the user clicks the mouse.\"></a></font><font size=+2> \r</font></font></li><li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>Submenus should \rbe shown when the mouse moves over the superordinate items. </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"menu-hierarchical1.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows a hierarchical menu where the subordinate menu pops up when its item in the superordinate menu is touched by the mouse cursor.\"></a></font></font></font></li><li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>Required \rformats of keyboard entries should be indicated. </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"table-example2.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows a computer form where the required format of the entries is clearly indicated.\"></a></font></font></font></font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">&nbsp;<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><a href=\"flawed-error-msg.htm\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\"></a></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></li>\r<li><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=+2>Potential adverse side effects\r      of      actions should be pointed out if the user may not be aware of them<font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"6\">, \r</font>and the user<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">'</font>s\rpermission  be requested. </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><a href=\"advance-info-long-duration.jpg\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows a warning that the indexing operation that the user requested is likely to take some while. The user is advised to perform the operation during the night and asked whether he or she wants to carry out the action nevertheless.\"></a> <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><a href=\"24-windows.pdf\"><img src=\"../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif\" width=\"11\" height=\"11\" border=\"0\" alt=\"The linked image shows a warning that the indexing operation that the user requested is likely to take some while. The user is advised to perform the operation during the night and asked whether he or she wants to carry out the action nevertheless.\"></a></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></li>\r</ul>\r</body>\r</html>\r", "encoding": "ascii"}